Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the coexistence of two wireless communication technologies, NR-U and WiGig, in a 60 GHz band. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture, making cs.NI the most likely category.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper may involve information theory concepts related to channel access mechanisms and coexistence of wireless technologies, making cs.IT a likely category.
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may involve multimedia applications that use the 60 GHz band, making cs.MM a possible category.
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may discuss security aspects of the coexistence of NR-U and WiGig, making cs.CR a possible category.
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - The paper may discuss the impact of the coexistence of NR-U and WiGig on society, making cs.COM a less likely but possible category.
